[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering initialization constraints**\n\nI'm thinking about whether HostProperties is already initialized since tests seem to use Conscrypt. The problem is JUnit doesn’t guarantee method ordering, which complicates things. Can I use the public API? No, that’s not an option. I should stick to the guideline of avoiding direct reflection unless the public API requires it, but this class is package-private. Even with that, it feels like we can still use it since there's no public API. Hmm, interesting.\n\n**Investigating class loading issues**\n\nI'm considering why previous attempts might not have counted if HostProperties.isOSX is false, which could be due to a fallback to a real class caused by a catch in a native image. In the JVM, I wonder if something is failing in isolation. I think I need to identify the catch, because it seems that `Class.forName` with os.name \"Mac OS X\" is trying to load NativeLibraryLoader, which interacts with the Platform class. I should check if the Platform class is static on JDK 21.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00bce2d44d0115720169f2a9ebaa2881a081448b93d1249f5b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8qn7yPoDNlxAbegnfChOq3ci-R_nNHWyBZghyhNoNRfqNHXVI65AK9w89L0wk_n_TKfRPNhYhcrDqIs9wsLYF1fGUlwlyPAYfOybILxgk-02rYIOPY2SO8w_VQElnzEzIkmrajn53X6IKf7gaSgu8KD1shztadoh05XM8kBxwXArokvWenSb6552-xQ1S4KN8eb2RJqSOVX7A4RKmkXcMs3MBdserdtK_jn0lBH11OVUW6V2UiTjCUfFeOZZGC5tDnCw67blQlOfm6X_IXwd3piwwHR75WYprEE8f8lj8J7_J7ZL8BAWIMS5jkFjKtbRPdw8-pk3QYGuR_xol8hbEG2_ABhR9UoEFDNqtzw9y6SyRcZDuE3stWDcwkguMHp4gigSdAFE8BCaiVTf_GoqRx6d5zUL3MTzqwm17k_GVQBwHtjMOJmppfNojEru3-340iIatRG4811eDOBAw17qkj6zItQVfI9sBrtD4MvkHHX32EnhPl-Ii9pvSZ1thKIzJWOaFsSpBw5nOCGQdrunYzp_ob-gG_szcSZlghqvU5RphpKFIEgeZG4ZAhb-K3lNY7h-b0skbwRpWnZ2KtMhJoe2nv-fI2SR-CCIpjJEpqwr3vSG0cywPjo8YG-4UUdLaWQRpj8i_XpfAwq12cUTCaR1qxjprdkSYWAD9fIwd112Wa7Apx4Pq4Z6jQu_9xpD6oaJBhAYjH